                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.48/1461: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-27T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 27, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>740. The following telegram has been sent to Bern: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>March 27, 8 p.m. Spain has now closed border to French refugees. For
                            purposes of comparison will you please inform me whether Swiss permit
                            refugees to cross into Switzerland and what treatment given those who
                            cross clandestinely? In particular, are they turned back into
                            France?</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Department and Algiers for Murphy.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
